name: QuickBooks Online
description: Add a QuickBooks Online Instance to connect your existing QuickBooks Online account to the Finance Hub, allowing you to manage your customers, employees, invoices, purchase orders etc. across multiple Finance Elements. You will need your QuickBooks Online account information to add an instance.
configDescription: If you do not have an QuickBooks account, you can create one at QuickBooks Signup

configuration.name: Authentication Type
configuration.description: Type of authentication to be used while connecting to Quickbooks

configuration.name: Authorization URL
configuration.defaultValue: com.intuit.quickbooks.accounting openid profile email phone address

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Use Sandbox
configuration.description: Sandbox Or Production. Select yes if you are using developer keys and connecting to a sandbox company

configuration.name: Refresh Time
configuration.description: Refresh Time in millisecs when it was last refreshed

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses.

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

configuration.name: Event Notification Subscription ID
configuration.description: The subscription ID for the webhook events subscription

configuration.name: Event poller refresh interval
configuration.description: Used for how often to poll the application (in minutes)

configuration.name: Callback Notification Signature Key
configuration.description: A key used to generate a validation hash header of the event/bulk notification webhook callback payload

parameters.name: asofdate
parameters.description: The as of date in format yyyy-mm-dd

parameters.name: returnCount
parameters.description: Pass true if total count is needed in response headers

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The page number. Defaults to 1 if not provided

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size. Default to 200 if not provided. Maximum of 2000

objects.name: paymentMethods
objects.description: The PaymentMethod resource provides the method of payment for received goods.

objects.name: attachments
objects.description: Notes and file attachments in the Finance system

objects.name: billPayments
objects.description: A BillPayment object represents the payment transaction for a bill that the business owner receives from a vendor for goods or services purchased from the vendor

objects.name: bills
objects.description: A Bill object is an AP transaction representing a request-for-payment from a third party for goods/services rendered, received, or both.

objects.name: budgets
objects.description: The Budget endpoint allows you to retrieve the current state of budgets already set up in the user's company file

objects.name: changes
objects.description: Find changed entity records in the Finance System

objects.name: classes
objects.description: Class objects provide a way to track different segments of the business so they're not tied to a particular client or project

objects.name: companies
objects.description: Search for the company in Quikbooks finance system

objects.name: companyInfo
objects.description: The CompanyInfo object contains basic company information

objects.name: count
objects.description: Mapped to Query on vendor side

objects.name: creditMemos
objects.description: The creditmemo object is a financial transaction representing a refund or credit of payment or part of a payment for goods or services that have been sold.

objects.name: creditTerms
objects.description: creditTerms is mapped to Terms. A Term object represents the terms under which a sale is made

objects.name: currencies
objects.description: Currencies is mapped to companycurrency. Currencies is applicable only for those companies that enable multicurrency, a companycurrency object defines a currency that is active in the QuickBooks Online company

objects.name: customers
objects.description: A customer is a consumer of the service or product that your business offers.

objects.name: departments
objects.description: The Department resource provides a way to track transactions based on physical locations such as stores, sales regions, or countries. As you create sales and expense transactions, consistently designate the department to which they belong.

objects.name: deposits
objects.description: A deposit object is a transaction that records one or more deposits of customer payment or direct deposit to account

objects.name: employees
objects.description: An Employee object represents a person working for the company.

objects.name: entitlements
objects.description: The Entitlements resource retrieves the features available to a company, identified by the company's ID

objects.name: estimates
objects.description: The Entitlements resource retrieves the features available to a company, identified by the company's

objects.name: exchangeRates
objects.description: Applicable only for those companies that enable multicurrency, the exchangerate resource provides the ability to query and set exchange rates available to the QuickBooks Online company.

objects.name: invoices
objects.description: An Invoice represents a sales form where the customer pays for a product or service later.

objects.name: invoicesVoid
objects.description: Void the invoice

objects.name: journalCodes
objects.description: JournalCodes in Quickbooks finicance system

objects.name: journalEntries
objects.description: JournalEntries in Quickbooks finicance system

objects.name: ledgerAccounts
objects.description: LedgerAccounts is Mapped to Accounts. An Account object is a component of a Chart Of Accounts, and is part of a ledger. It is used to record a total monetary amount allocated against a specific use. Accounts are one of five basic types: asset, liability, revenue (income), expenses, or equity.

objects.name: payments
objects.description: A Payment object records a payment in QuickBooks. The payment can be applied for a particular customer against multiple Invoices and Credit Memos. It can also be created without any Invoice or Credit Memo, by just specifying an amount

objects.name: paymentsVoid
objects.description: Voids a Payment

objects.name: preferences
objects.description: The Preferences resource represents a set of company preferences that control application behavior in QuickBooks Online

objects.name: products
objects.description: Products are mapped to Items. An item is a thing that your company buys, sells, or re-sells, such as products and services

objects.name: purchaseOrders
objects.description: The PurchaseOrder object is a non-posting transaction representing a request to purchase goods or services from a third party.

objects.name: purchases
objects.description: A Purchase object represents an expense, such as a purchase made from a vendor.

objects.name: refundReceipts
objects.description: A RefundReceipt object represents a refund to the customer for a product or service that was provided.

objects.name: reports
objects.description: reports of the company

objects.name: reportsMetadata
objects.description: metadata of the reports

objects.name: salesReceipts
objects.description: Sales Receipts of the comapny in Quickbooks system

objects.name: taxAgencies
objects.description: A TaxAgency object is associated with a tax rate and identifies the agency to which that tax rate applies, that is, the entity that collects those taxes.

objects.name: taxCodes
objects.description: A TaxCode object is used to track the taxable or non-taxable status of products, services, and customers

objects.name: taxRates
objects.description: A TaxRate object represents rate applied to calculate tax liability. Use the TaxService entity to create a taxrate. See Global tax model for more information about using TaxRate objects and the tax model in general.

objects.name: taxService
objects.description: The TaxService resource allows you to perform create TaxCode object or TaxRate Object

objects.name: timeActivities
objects.description: The TimeActivity object represents a record of time worked by a vendor or employee.

objects.name: transfers
objects.description: A Transfer represents a transaction where funds are moved between two accounts from the company's QuickBooks chart of accounts.

objects.name: vendorCredits
objects.description: The VendorCredit object is an accounts payable transaction that represents a refund or credit of payment for goods or services. It is a credit that a vendor owes you for various reasons such as overpaid bill, returned merchandise, or other reasons.

objects.name: vendors
objects.description: The Vendor object represents the seller from whom your company purchases any service or product.
